A warrant officer , based in Mthatha , and a security guard were killed last night when a car they were travelling in overturned between Tsolo and Maclear. Mthatha police spokesman Lieutenant &#8211; Colonel Mzukisi Fatyela said the incident happened near Ntywenka around 10.30pm. The deceased policeman, 35, was working in the Madeira police station while the security guard worked for a private company. &#8220;The policeman was working out of Madeira police station in Mthatha. He worked as a court orderly in Maclear and was returning from court there when the incident happened.&#8221; Fatyela however could not give out the name of the deceased policeman until his next of kin had been notified .